3. William Adey's giving Money to Brown's Son, to prevent his Father's Diſcovery, leſt it ſhould void Mr. Pauncefort's Election;
                  His Giving and Paying Money for Mr. Pauncefort.
                   and going with Mr. Pauncefort to Alderman Hays, where Mr. Pauncefort Treated his own Voters, and two of Mr. Howard's, to procure Subſcriptions, That he had given no Bribes: And William Adey paid 20 s. to Mr. Hays, towards what was drunk at his Houſe upon that Account.
